UID:2bM-P3P3xuZ3GFSkiw9cf
SUMMARY:Kickstands Up! Gallery Tour with Dykes on Bikes
DTSTAMP:20260307T070341Z
DTSTART:20260307T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Dive deeper into Kickstands Up: 125 Years of Motorcycling in th
	e Pacific Northwest with a gallery talk by a Monkey\\\, Ride Captain from 
	Seattle Dykes on Bikes Womxn’s Motorcycle Club. Learn more about the organ
	ization’s history in the fight for LGBTQ+ rights and the bikes that hold a
	 special place in their hearts. \\nSpots are limited and are assigned on a
	 first-come\\\, first-served basis. \\nFor accessibility support\\\, pleas
	e contact programs@mohai.org two weeks before the event. \\nPhoto: MOHAI\\
	\, Seattle Post-Intelligencer Collection\\\, 2000.107.19930627.5.15\\\, by
	 Gilbert W. Arias\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/kickstands-up-gallery-tour-wi
	th-dykes-on-bikes/\n\nFrom MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/kickstands-up-gallery-tour-with-dykes-on-bikes/
LOCATION:MOHAI\\\, MOHAI - 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98109\\\,
	 United States
